22/03/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- A two-day international forum titled "Global Terrorism and International Co-operation" opens Thursday (23 March) in Ankara.
Senior military and political representatives from 28 states are expected to attend.
In other news, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan has repeated that Turkey will not open its airspace and ports to Greek Cypriot planes and ships until steps are taken to end the international isolation of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus.
His comments appeared in an interview with the Austrian weekly magazine Profile.
(NTV, Focus - 22/03/06;
Darik, TurkishPress.com - 21/03/06)
